{{Infobox language |name=Ese |region=[[Papua New Guinea]] |ethnicity= |speakers=10,000 |date=2000 |ref=e18 |speakers2=4,000 monolinguals (no date)<ref name=e16>{{e16|mcq}}</ref><!--no idea where this comes from. had been 50% monolingual--> |familycolor=Papuan |fam1=[[Trans–New Guinea languages|Trans–New Guinea]] |fam2=[[Koiarian languages|Koiarian]] |fam3=Baraic |iso3=mcq |glotto=esee1247 |glottorefname=Ese }}
'''Ese''', or '''Managalasi''', is a language of [[Papua New Guinea]]. Dialects are Muaturaina, Chimona, Dea, Akabafa, Nami, Mesari, Averi, Afore, Minjori, Oko, Wakue, Numba, Jimuni, Karira. Perhaps 40% of speakers are monolingual.
