Though it is said that [[Japanese people|Ethnic Japanese]] make up 98.5% of the total population and that the rest are Koreans 0.5%, Chinese 0.4%, other 0.6%,<ref name="CIATONGA">{{cite web|url= https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/ja.html|title= East & Southeast Asia :: JAPAN|publisher= CIA The World Factbook}}</ref> in fact these numbers are not known. The Ministry of Justice in Japan conflates nationality with ethnicity, and they have no official data on the actual ethnic breakdown of people in Japan.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Arudou|first1=Debito|title=Census blind to Japan’s true diversity|url=http://www.japantimes.co.jp/community/2010/10/05/issues/census-blind-to-japans-true-diversity/#.VxQMVXLALFZ|accessdate=17 April 2016|publisher=''[[The Japan Times]]''|date=5 October 2010}}</ref>

