==Chinese==
{{Main article|Chinese in Japan}}
[[Chinese people in Japan]] are the one of the largest ethnic minority in Japan. They comprise 0.52% of Japan's population. Chinese people are mostly concentrated in [[Osaka]], [[Tokyo]], and [[Yokohama]] areas.

==Ainu==
{{Main article|Ainu people}}
The [[Ainu people|Ainu]] is an aboriginal ethnic Japanese tribe that make up a portion of the Japanese demography

==Brazilians==
{{Main article|Brazilians in Japan}}
There is a significant community of [[Brazilians]] in Japan, which is home to the second largest [[Brazilian diaspora|Brazilian community outside of Brazil]]. They also constitute the largest number of [[Portuguese language in Asia|Portuguese speakers in Asia]], even greater than those of formerly Portuguese [[East Timor]], [[Macau|Macao]] and [[Goa]] combined. Likewise, [[Brazil]] maintains its status as home to the largest Japanese community outside of Japan.

